		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are many map editors available that have customizable output, such as <a href="http://www.mapeditor.org/" class="postlink">Tiled</a> or <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20110706215126/http://opentume.co.cc/" class="postlink">Open tUME</a>. You could use those to export data for whatever platform you need.
<br />
<br />You can also write your own map editor. Or write a program that analyses a BMP, where the colour of a pixel corresponds to the appropriate tile. Then you can use a simple paint program as your map editor.
<br />
<br />...but if you're writing a port, why do you need a level editor at all? Why not just use the level data from the original ROM?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


