		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Instead, I'd prefer to make a heroic attempt to swing it back onto topic. If <em>that</em> doesn't work, the alternative is standing by: <img src="http://pics.pineight.com/dwi/dancing_lock.gif" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />There exist plenty of generic map editors. They work for any game whose underlying world model is essentially a 2D array: the converter just has to understand the compression scheme that the game engine uses. They don't work for games that have an object-based world model like SMB series, where a converter would have a much harder time recognizing arbitrarily placed objects optimally.

		

